Based on https://w3-o.cs.hm.edu/users/ruckert/public_html/web2w/

Add this `mf' script to PATH:

    #!/bin/sh
    /path/to/mf/plain "$@"
    ret=$?
    [ $ret != 134 ] && echo
    exit $ret

Add the following to .bashrc:
  export SCREEN_SIZE=$(xrandr 2>/dev/null|grep connected|grep -o '[0-9]\+x[0-9]\+')
and use the companion repo http://github.com/igor-liferenko/mf-wayland
(set path to it in screen.ch)

To use debugger, add "-g -Og" and run "gdb plain"

Compile ctangle (using common.patch and ctangle.patch) and wmerge from:

    http://ftp.cs.stanford.edu/pub/cweb/cweb-3.64ag.tgz

Adjust base_default_length, base_area_length and paths in path.ch
Adjust path to TeXfonts in Makefile

Change-files are for Linux; `em' editor is needed:

    https://github.com/igor-liferenko/em

-----------------------------------

Other WEB programs converted to CWEB:

    https://github.com/igor-liferenko/tex
    https://github.com/igor-liferenko/dvitype
